> POSIX requires some commands to be callable via exec().

Solaris 10 has the following amusing implementation (/usr/bin/cd):

#!/bin/ksh -p
#
#ident  "@(#)alias.sh   1.2     00/02/15 SMI"
#
# Copyright (c) 1995 by Sun Microsystems, Inc.
#
cmd=`basename $0`
$cmd "$@"

